 {"id":"bd-9zg6j","title":"fuzz: add fuzz_inode_roundtrip for ffs-inode serialize/parse","description":"ffs_inode has serialize_inode (lib.rs:136) but no fuzz coverage. Create round-trip fuzz target: parse inode from bytes, serialize back, verify equality. Also fuzz encode_extra_timestamp.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-22T13:21:09.193566254Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-22T23:52:58.213216336Z","closed_at":"2026-04-22T23:52:58.213216336Z","close_reason":"Added fuzz_inode_roundtrip plus seeded corpus, exposed a doc-hidden deterministic serialize hook in ffs-inode for fuzz-only roundtrips, and verified with rch cargo check --manifest-path fuzz/Cargo.toml --bin fuzz_inode_roundtrip and rch cargo clippy --manifest-path fuzz/Cargo.toml --bin fuzz_inode_roundtrip -- -D warnings","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"bd-a0s78","title":"add mounted-path ext4 read-only EROFS coverage for fsync fdatasync and fsyncdir","description":"Survey finding: fuse_e2e currently proves ext4 fsync, fdatasync, and fsyncdir success on writable mounts, while ffs-fuse and ffs-core already enforce read-only rejection paths with EROFS. Scope: add read-only ext4 mounted-path probes for file sync_all, sync_data, and directory sync_all that assert exact EROFS and unchanged directory/data state. Acceptance: ext4 FUSE E2E freezes operator-visible read-only sync refusal for fsync, fdatasync, and fsyncdir.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"ubuntu","created_at":"2026-04-21T08:19:55.141375557Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-22T05:26:00Z","closed_at":"2026-04-22T05:26:00Z","close_reason":"Stale in-progress sweep: no commit reference after more than 12 hours; closed per operator instruction so the work can be re-filed or reclaimed cleanly.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"bd-a5wh","title":"Add error-path and edge-case tests for ffs-extent mark_written/punch_hole/allocate_unwritten","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-20T00:58:16.399872340Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-20T01:03:49.807745171Z","closed_at":"2026-02-20T01:03:49.807726286Z","close_reason":"Added 4 new edge-case tests: mark_written on already-written extents, mark_written on empty tree, punch_hole in unwritten extent, full unwritten lifecycle (allocate-mark-truncate). All 26 tests pass.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"bd-a6bgm","title":"btrfs BTRFS_IOC_DEV_INFO mounted-path parity proof","description":"Follow-up to bd-ckgtr: the DEV_INFO ioctl support was closed with unit dispatch tests, but its acceptance required mounted-path E2E coverage. Add a FUSE mounted-path conformance probe for BTRFS_IOC_DEV_INFO, verify the returned devid/uuid/total/bytes_used/path contract, and update FEATURE_PARITY evidence.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-26T01:13:38.787439422Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-26T01:20:46.524944818Z","closed_at":"2026-04-26T01:20:46.522987213Z","close_reason":"Added mounted-path BTRFS_IOC_DEV_INFO parity probe for wildcard, exact devid+uuid, and missing-device ENODEV contracts; updated FEATURE_PARITY evidence. Validation: cargo fmt --check; ubs crates/ffs-harness/tests/fuse_e2e.rs FEATURE_PARITY.md; git diff --check; rch exec -- cargo test -p ffs-harness --test fuse_e2e btrfs_fuse_ioctl_dev_info_via_mounted_path -- --nocapture; rch exec -- cargo test -p ffs-harness parity_report_matches_feature_parity_md; rch exec -- cargo check --workspace --all-targets; rch exec -- cargo clippy --workspace --all-targets -- -D warnings.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["btrfs","parity","porting"]}
 {"id":"bd-a8fzc","title":"add mounted-path btrfs SEEK_DATA/SEEK_HOLE edge-case coverage for fully-allocated and leading-hole files","description":"Survey finding: btrfs mounted-path seek coverage currently proves only the punched-middle-hole scenario, but OpenFs::btrfs_lseek_data/hole also implements fully allocated and leading-hole cases. Scope: add btrfs FUSE probes that freeze SEEK_HOLE on a fully allocated file returning the virtual EOF hole, and SEEK_DATA/SEEK_HOLE on a file with a leading sparse hole returning the next data offset and hole start correctly, including EOF ENXIO behavior. Acceptance: btrfs FUSE E2E covers these sparse-layout edge cases with exact offsets.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-21T08:10:59.453875131Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-21T18:59:55.432979683Z","closed_at":"2026-04-21T18:59:55.431125654Z","close_reason":"done","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
